#MEM id=quinn source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/quinn/TOOLS.md savings=-2%
M|Memo|tx|qn reads and writes memory via `/ap/settings` — never directly to sb.
M|Memo|**Re|**
M|Memo|tx|```
M|Memo|tx|GET /ap/settings?tp=memory&agentId=qn-qa&ventureId={activeVenture}
M|Memo|tx|```
M|Memo|**Wr|**
M|Memo|tx|```json
M|Memo|tx|POST /ap/settings
M|Memo|tx|{
M|Memo|tp|"memory",
M|Memo|"age|"qn-qa",
M|Memo|"ven|"{activeVenture}",
M|Memo|"key|"approval_history",
M|Memo|"val|"Phase 3: APPROVED 2026-03-22. bd + lint passed. All AC met."
M|Memo|tx|}
M|Memo|tx|```
M|Memo|Afte|edit the Live State table in `MEMORY.md` to match.
M|Memo|tx|---
M|Supa|tx|qn uses sb to verify that data was actually written correctly — not just that the ap returned 200.
M|Supa|**Us|**
M|Supa|- Af|query `social_stats` to confirm data exists for the vt
M|Supa|- Af|query `messages` to confirm the conversation was saved correctly
M|Supa|- Af|query `briefs` to confirm the brief was written
M|Supa|it|Verify that a memory pin wrote to `agent_memory` w/ the correct `agent_id` and `venture_id`
M|Supa|it|Check that a "Clear History" action deleted the correct rows (not more, not less)
M|Supa|**Ke|**
M|Supa|tx|```sql
M|Supa|tx|-- Verify message was saved
M|Supa|tx|SELECT * FROM messages
M|Supa|tx|WHERE conversation_id = '[tst-conversation-id]'
M|Supa|tx|ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT 5;
M|Supa|tx|-- Verify brief was created
M|Supa|tx|SELECT id, venture_id, date, read_at FROM briefs
M|Supa|tx|ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT 3;
M|Supa|tx|-- Verify sl stats exist for vt
M|Supa|tx|SELECT platform, fetched_at FROM social_stats
M|Supa|tx|WHERE venture_id = '[vt-id]';
M|Supa|tx|-- Verify ag memory was written
M|Supa|tx|SELECT key, value, updated_at FROM agent_memory
M|Supa|tx|WHERE agent_id = '[ag-id]' AND venture_id = '[vt-id]';
M|Supa|tx|```
M|GitH|tx|qn uses GitHub to file structured bug reports for every ❌ bug found during QA.
M|GitH|**Us|**
M|GitH|it|cr a GitHub issue for every bug qn cannot fix herself (she proposes the fix in the issue body)
M|GitH|it|Tag issues w/ `bug`, `phase-N`, and the responsible developer label
M|GitH|it|Link issues back to qn's MEMORY.md QA verdict log
M|GitH|it|Check if a previously filed bug has been resolved before re-testing
M|GitH|**Ke|**
M|GitH|tx|```
M|GitH|tx|create_issue          → file a structured bug rp w/ steps to reproduce + fix proposal
M|GitH|tx|list_issues           → see open bugs before starting a re-tst
M|GitH|tx|close_issue           → close after confirming rj/mi's fix resolved the bug
M|GitH|tx|```
M|GitH|tx|---
M|Buil|Quin|
M|Buil|tx|```bash
M|Buil|tx|npm run bd     # must complete w/ zero er
M|Buil|tx|npm run lint      # must complete w/ zero warnings
M|Buil|tx|```
M|Buil|tx|Both must pass in the same sn where APPROVED is issued. A passing bd from yesterday does not count.
M|Buil|tx|---
M|Rout|tx|\| rt \| Method \| When \|
M|Rout|tx|\|-------\|--------\|------\|
M|Rout|tx|\| `/ap/settings` \| GET \| sn start — read own memory (edge cases, lint patterns, approval history) \|
M|Rout|tx|\| `/ap/settings` \| POST \| After every QA sn to up bug_log, approval_history, known_edge_cases \|
M|Rout|tx|qn does not write to any other rt. She reads from all rt as part of testing, but only writes memory via `/ap/settings`.
M|Rout|tx|---
M|Reac|tx|qn runs `rc-doctor` after every code change to get a structured health rp before issuing APPROVED.
M|Reac|**In|** `npm install rc-doctor` (already installed in project)
M|Reac|**Ru|**
M|Reac|tx|```bash
M|Reac|tx|npx rc-doctor -y --json . > rc-doctor-rp.json
M|Reac|tx|```
M|Reac|**Ru|**
M|Reac|tx|```bash
M|Reac|tx|npx rc-doctor -y --diff main --json . > rc-doctor-rp.json
M|Reac|tx|```
M|Reac|**Ru|**
M|Reac|tx|```bash
M|Reac|tx|npx rc-doctor -y --staged --json .
M|Reac|tx|```
M|Reac|**Ke|**
M|Reac|it|`--json` — machine-readable output for parsing
M|Reac|it|`--diff main` — scan only changed files vs main
M|Reac|it|`--staged` — scan only git staged files
M|Reac|it|`--blocking wn` — fail on warnings too
M|Reac|it|`--dead-code` — detect unused files/exports/deps
M|Reac|it|`--no-score` — skip score ap (offline safe)
M|Reac|**Wh|**
M|Reac|tx|1. After any code change (tsc clean) → run rc-doctor diff scan
M|Reac|tx|2. Before issuing APPROVED → run full scan
M|Reac|tx|3. Weekly Pulse → include rc-doctor score tn
M|Reac|tx|4. PR rv → attach JSON rp as artifact
M|Reac|**QA|** After `npx tsc --noEmit` and `npm run lint` pass, run `npx rc-doctor -y --diff main --json .` and verify zero er before APPROVED.
M|Reac|tx|---
